title: Summerfield
description:
Summerfield is a 1977 Australian thriller, directed by Ken Hannam, written by Cliff Green (who wrote the screenplay for Picnic At Hanging Rock) and produced by Patricia Lovell . It stars Nick Tate, Elizabeth Alexander, John Waters, Charles 'Bud' Tingwell, Max Fairchild and Geraldine Turner. Summerfield was filmed on location on Phillip Island and Churchill Island in Victoria.

The story begins with Simon Robinson arriving in a small seaside community to take over as teacher at the local school. He makes the acquaintance of the siblings Jenny and David Abbott, and Jenny's daughter Sally, who live on the isolated island estate of Summerfield. The discovery that his predecessor vanished and, that Sally has a rare blood disorder lead Simon to try to uncover the truth behind the mystery.

Extras: A Shattered Silence, Secrets of Summerfield and a theatrical trailer
